1. This API receives a **GET request to call any LinkedIn API dynamically**.
2. The request must include an **Authorization header (Bearer token)**.
3. It also receives a **LinkedIn API URL as a request parameter**.
4. The controller **extracts the access token from the Authorization header**.
5. The token is passed to the **service along with the API URL**.
6. The service uses **WebClient to call the given LinkedIn API URL**.
7. It adds the **Authorization header (Bearer token) to authenticate the request**.
8. It also sets the **LinkedIn API version header**.
9. The LinkedIn API **returns the requested data as a response**.
10. The system **captures and returns that response to the frontend**.
